        <img src="/assets/cherry-crisp.jpg">
        <h5>Ingredients</h5>
<ul class="ingredients">
  <li class="ingredient">Filling:</li>
  <li class="ingredient">3-4 cups sweet cherries, pitted</li>
  <li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons maple syrup</li>
  <li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons whole wheat flour</li>
  <li class="ingredient">Topping:</li>
  <li class="ingredient">1/2 cup oats</li>
  <li class="ingredient">1/4 cup whole wheat flour</li>
  <li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons sucanat</li>
  <li class="ingredient">1/2 teaspoons baking soda</li>
  <li class="ingredient">2 tablespoons butter, melted</li>
</ul>
<h5>Instructions</h5>
<div class="instructions">
<ol>
  <li class="instruction">Preheat oven to 375˚.</li>
  <li class="instruction">In a medium bowl, combine filling ingredients slightly mashing the cherries and combing the flour and maple syrup. Divide into two 4" ramekins.</li>
  <li class="instruction">In a separate bowl combine the dry topping ingredients and stir in the melted butter until everything is well combined. Divide the topping over each ramekin.</li>
  <li class="instruction">Bake for 30-35 minutes until topping is golden and the cherry filling is bubbly. Serve while still warm.</li>
</ol>
</div>
